The paper deals with video summarization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep neural networks for encoding semantic features is a common technique in multimedia analysis (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of descriptions, which suggests a possible application of natural language processing (cs.CL). The evaluation of the proposed method involves comparing it to baseline approaches, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of finding important or informative parts of a video, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
